"title": "7028: church, life of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7028",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The church lives its life in union with Christ and in the power of the Holy Spirit. It is called to mutual love, holy living, and to worship.</p>\n<h2>The church lives its life in union with Christ</h2>\n<h3>The church lives in Christ and Christ lives in the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:30\">1CO 1:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:20\">MAT 18:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:5\">JHN 15:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:21\">JHN 17:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:6\">1CO 8:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:20\">GAL 2:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:27\">COL 1:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:6\">COL 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:13\">1JN 4:13</a></p>\n<h3>Believers are united with Christ in baptism</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:27\">GAL 3:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:38\">ACT 2:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:5\">ACT 19:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:3-Rom6:4\">ROM 6:3–6:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:12\">COL 2:12</a></p>\n<h2>The church lives its life in the power of the Holy Spirit</h2>\n<h3>The church lives in the Spirit, and the Spirit lives in the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:9-Rom8:11\">ROM 8:9–8:11</a></strong> <em>The indwelling Spirit is identified with the presence of Jesus Christ.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:16\">1CO 3:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:16\">GAL 5:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:25\">GAL 5:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:22\">EPH 2:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:14\">2TI 1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:27\">1JN 2:27</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit is given to the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:4-Acts1:5\">ACT 1:4–1:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:22\">JHN 20:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:4\">ACT 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:8\">ACT 15:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:6\">ROM 7:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:16\">ROM 15:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:11\">1CO 6:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:3\">GAL 3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:1-1Pet1:2\">1PE 1:1–1:2</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit seals the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:13\">EPH 1:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:22\">2CO 1:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:5\">2CO 5:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:30\">EPH 4:30</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit guides the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:7\">REV 2:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:29\">ACT 8:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:19\">ACT 10:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:12\">ACT 11:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:2\">ACT 13:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:23\">ACT 20:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:4\">ACT 21:4</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit teaches the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:13\">1CO 2:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:13\">JHN 16:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:17\">EPH 1:17</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit sanctifies the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:16\">ROM 15:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:11\">1CO 6:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:13\">2TH 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:2\">1PE 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit endows the church with gifts</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:7\">1CO 12:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:6-Rom12:8\">ROM 12:6–12:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:8-1Cor12:11\">1CO 12:8–12:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:28\">1CO 12:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:11\">EPH 4:11</a></p>\n<h2>The church as a fellowship</h2>\n<h3>As a fellowship of mutual love</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:11\">1TH 5:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:2\">ROM 15:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:12\">1CO 14:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:10\">GAL 6:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:18\">1TH 4:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:25\">HEB 10:25</a></p>\n<h3>As a fellowship of ordinary people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:26-1Cor1:27\">1CO 1:26–1:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:20\">LUK 6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:5\">JAS 2:5</a></p>\n<h2>The distinctiveness of the church</h2>\n<h3>The church as a chosen people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:9\">1PE 2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:4\">EPH 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:12\">COL 3:12</a></p>\n<h3>The church as a holy people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:14\">HEB 12:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:16\">ROM 11:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:16\">ROM 15:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:2\">1CO 1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:21\">EPH 2:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:3\">EPH 5:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:13\">1TH 3:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:11\">HEB 2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:15-1Pet1:16\">1PE 1:15–1:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:11\">2PE 3:11</a></p>\n<h3>The church as a people set apart</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor7:1\">2CO 7:1</a></strong> <em>The repeated call to be separate from evil is the practical outworking of the church's sanctification.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:9-1Cor5:12\">1CO 5:9–5:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:14-2Cor6:18\">2CO 6:14–6:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:7\">EPH 5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:14\">2TH 3:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:1-2Tim3:5\">2TI 3:1–3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:10-Titus3:11\">TIT 3:10–3:11</a></p>\n<h3>The church as a heavenly people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:14-John17:16\">JHN 17:14–17:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:20\">LUK 10:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:48\">1CO 15:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:26\">GAL 4:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:6\">EPH 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:20\">PHP 3:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:1-Col3:4\">COL 3:1–3:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:16\">HEB 11:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:22-Heb12:23\">HEB 12:22–12:23</a></p>\n<h2>The church and worship</h2>\n<h3>Praise in the life of the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:15\">HEB 13:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:47\">ACT 2:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:26\">1CO 14:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:18-Eph5:20\">EPH 5:18–5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:3\">PHP 3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:16\">COL 3:16</a></p>\n<h3>Prayer in the life of the church</h3>\n<p>Corporate prayer in the church:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:14\">ACT 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:42\">ACT 2:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:24-Acts4:31\">ACT 4:24–4:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:5\">ACT 12:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:12\">ACT 12:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:36\">ACT 20:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:5\">ACT 21:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:30\">ROM 15:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:19-Eph6:20\">EPH 6:19–6:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:2-Col4:4\">COL 4:2–4:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:25\">1TH 5:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:1\">2TH 3:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:18\">HEB 13:18</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:18\">EPH 6:18</a> <em>prayer for all Christians</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:1-1Tim2:2\">1TI 2:1–2:2</a> <em>prayer for all, including secular leaders</em></p>\n<h2>Baptism in the life of the church</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:38\">ACT 2:38</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:13\">1CO 1:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:26-Gal3:27\">GAL 3:26–3:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:4-Eph4:5\">EPH 4:4–4:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:11-Col2:12\">COL 2:11–2:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:21\">1PE 3:21</a></p>\n<h3>The Lord's Supper in the life of the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:16-1Cor10:17\">1CO 10:16–10:17</a></strong> <em>The breaking of bread was central to the church's worship and a vital expression of its fellowship.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:42\">ACT 2:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:46\">ACT 2:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:7\">ACT 20:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:21\">1CO 10:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:17-1Cor11:34\">1CO 11:17–11:34</a></p>\n<h2>The suffering of the church</h2>\n<h3>Suffering persecution from a hostile world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:33\">JHN 16:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:10-Matt5:12\">MAT 5:10–5:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:12\">1CO 4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:9\">2CO 4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:4\">1TH 3:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:12\">2TI 3:12</a></p>\n<h3>Sharing in the sufferings of Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:10\">PHP 3:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:20\">JHN 15:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:17\">ROM 8:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:10-2Cor4:11\">2CO 4:10–4:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:13\">1PE 4:13</a></p>\n<h3>Suffering as the road to glory</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:12\">JAS 1:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:3\">ROM 5:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:18\">ROM 8:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:17\">2CO 4:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:11-2Tim2:12\">2TI 2:11–2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:10\">1PE 5:10</a></p>",
